<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>Factorise the following quadratic expression:
<me>
{4 x^2+17 x+4}
</me>
</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We want to factorise:
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4 x^2+17 x+4}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Identify the coefficients.
</p>

<p>
Coefficient of <m>x^2</m> = <m>{4}</m>
</p>

<p>
Coefficient of <m>x</m> = <m>{17}</m>
</p>

<p>
Constant term = <m>{4}</m>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Multiply the coefficient of <m>x^2</m> and the constant.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4} \times {4} = {16}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Find two numbers whose product is <m>{16}</m> and whose sum is <m>{17}</m>.
</p>

<p>
These numbers are <m>{16}</m> and <m>{1}</m>.
</p>

<p>
Step 4: Split the middle term.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4}x^2 + {16}x + {1}x + {4}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 5: Factorise by grouping.
</p>

<p>
<me>
{4}x(x + {4}) + {1}(x + {4})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 6: Factor the common bracket.
</p>

<p>
<me>
({4}x + {1})(x + {4})
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>\left(x+4\right) \left(4 x+1\right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>